creator: Various
description:
LibriVox recording of Short Poetry Collection 137 by Various.
Read in English by Winston Tharp; Ian King; Leonard Wilson; Son of the Exiles; Algy Pug; Shakira Searle; Ben Adams; Kangaroo692; Bruce Kachuk; John N. Daily This is a collection of 26 poems read by LibriVox volunteers for October 2014. This collection includes the following: After a Journey, by Thomas Hardy Autumn Prophecy, by J. M. March The Broken Fountain, by Amy Lowell Choice, by Angela Morgan The Dead Democrat, by George Essex Evans Don Juan Declaims, by James Elroy Flecker Elaine, by Edna St. Vincent Millay Evening, by Hilda Doolittle The Horseman, by Walter De la Mare In Hospital, by James Elroy Flecker The Lake Isle of Innisfree, by William Butler Yeats The Market-Girl, by Thomas Hardy Mid-day, by Hilda Doolittle Night, by Hilda Doolittle The Night Wind, by Eugene Field Out in the Fields with God, by Anonymous Overtones, by William Alexander Percy The Parrot, by James Elroy Flecker Say Not The Struggle Naught Availeth, by Arthur Hugh Clough September 1918, by Amy Lowell Some one, by Walter De la Mare Sonnet III (I know I am but summer to your heart), by Edna St. Vincent Millay Sonnet VIII (Say what you will, and scratch my heart to find), by Edna St. Vincent Millay The Time I’ve Lost in Wooing, by Thomas Moore To His Wife, by Su Wu Weathers, by Thomas Hardy For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
